membership:
Glass for Europe is a member of Glass Alliance Europe: www.glassallianceeurope.eu .&#xd;
Glass for Europe is part of the Coalition for Energy Savings and a contributor to the Renovate Europe Campaign.&#xd;
Glass for Europe is also a member of Construction Products Europe and CLEPA as glass manufacturers supply both the construction and automotive sectors.

memberOrga:
Can be members of Glass for Europe companies which operate flat glass manufacturing plants in the EU. Out of six companies meeting this criteria, five are members of Glass for Europe: AGC Glass Europe, Guardian, NSG Group, Saint-Gobain Glass and Sisecam.&#xd;
Additionally, national associations of a member country of the EU representing flat glass processors and transformers can become national partners.&#xd;
Companies involved in glass processing can become corporate partners of Glass for Europe.&#xd;
The full list of members and partners is accessible via this link: https://glassforeurope.com/about-us/members/
